properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 12 at 11:08PM CST until January 13 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Wichita KS
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...Butler County.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
Due to low temperatures, expect some slick conditions as the
fog is likely to freeze to road surfaces.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...This dense fog is expected to expand into
all of the warned area. Due to the cold temperatures, expect
freezing fog in the warned area. Use caution on roadways as
they may become slick. Slow down and increase following
distance for safety.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST MONDAY
